is also true that Hazel Shade resembled me in certain respects.





Lines 367-370: then—pen, again—explain


In speech John Shade, as a good American, rhymed “again” with “pen” and not with “explain.” The adjacent position of these rhymes is curious.





Line 376: poem


I believe I can guess (in my bookless mountain cave) what poem is meant; but without looking it up I would not wish to name its author. Anyway, I deplore my friend’s vicious thrusts at the most distinguished 